🧩 3. Structured logging to disk (on Quest)

Cursor MUST implement:

- Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/TelemetryLogger.cs

Requirements:

- Writes logs to a file named MQ3.log in Application.persistentDataPath.  
- Each log entry is a single JSON line:

`json
{"ts":"2026-05-02T07:22:10Z","sub":"XR","sev":"INFO","msg":"OpenXR loader initialised"}
`

- Expose static methods:

`csharp
TelemetryLogger.Info(string subsystem, string message);
TelemetryLogger.Warn(string subsystem, string message);
TelemetryLogger.Error(string subsystem, string message, Exception ex = null);
`

- All major subsystems MUST use this logger:
  - XR initialisation  
  - Passthrough permission  
  - Passthrough start  
  - AR camera setup  
  - HUD init  
  - Mode controllers  
  - PathTracker  
  - CoverageMap  
  - AI network layer  

---

🧩 4. Log rotation (MQ3.log → MQ3.1.log, etc.)

TelemetryLogger MUST:

- Check file size before each write.  
- If MQ3.log > 10 MB:
  - Move MQ3.log → MQ3.1.log (or increment index).  
  - Start a new MQ3.log.  

Rotation can be simple (e.g. keep last 3–5 files).

